relation: Enters configuration change logger configuration mode.
Enables the logging of configuration changes.
Specifies the maximum number of entries retained in the configuration log.
Enables the sending of notifications of configuration changes to a remote syslog.
Displays entries from the configuration log.

Examples The following example, shows how to set the file privilege level to 3 and verify the change using the show running-config command.  Device(config)# file privilege ? <0-15> Privilege level Device(config)# file privilege 3 Device(config)# end Device# show running-config | i file priv file privilege 3 Related Commands Command Description privilege level Sets the default privilege level for a line. file prompt To specify the level of prompting, use the file promptcommand in global configuration mode. file prompt prompt [ alert | noisy
